So I'm sitting in the Oasis hoping to find a group. My character is a level 16 cleric wearing patchwork and using a summoned hammer, so the only thing I can solo is a caimen. I happen to see one pass by the docks, I root it, nuke it 3 times then head in to finish it off in melee.<br>
<br>
As I approach the caimen I see a monk run up to it and start hitting it. I finish it off with my hammer and see this:<br>
Shewina makes a rude gesture at a caimen corpse.<br>
You say, in elvish, &quot;What was that for?&quot;<br>
Shewina makes a rude gesture.<br>
You say, in elvish, &quot;I was just finishing of my kill.&quot;<br>
Shewina makes a rude gesture at you.<br>
.... Shewina then runs off to wherever...<br>
<br>
Now this is a tiny episode of no importance, but due to my not being able to communicate, I probably took a faction hit with the Order of the Oaken (her guild). I don't think I stole anything from her, the caimen was just walking by when I rooted it, but I'm not positive. I was at my maximum casting distance so it is possible I KS'd it from her if I didn't see her.<br>
<br>
So I stood there for a moment, realizing there was no way to fix this misunderstanding and just went on with my evening. For some reason this just really got under my skin. <br>
